{{Korean name|Kim}} {{Infobox person |name = |image = |caption = |birth_date = April 22, 1945 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = President of the [[Boy Scouts of Korea]] |spouse = |nationality = |module3 = {{Infobox Korean name | hangul = 김석원 | hanja = 金錫元 | rr = Gim Seogwon | mr = Kim Sŏgwŏn | image = | caption = | hangulho =창제 | hanjaho =倉齊 | rrho =Changje | mrho =Ch'angje | koreanipaho = | child = yes}} }}
'''Kim Suk-won''' ({{Korean|김석원|金錫元}}; born April 22, 1945) was the chair of [[Ssangyong]] Business Group, one of the largest companies in the [[Republic of Korea]],<ref name="brandeis1">{{cite web |url=http://www.brandeis.edu/ibs/about_advantage.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-10-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070805013544/http://www.brandeis.edu/ibs/about_advantage.php |archivedate=2007-08-05 |df= }}</ref> served as the President of the [[Boy Scouts of Korea]], a member of the [[World Scout Committee]], and Vice-Chairman of the [[World Scout Foundation]].
In 1995, Kim was awarded the 241st ''[[Bronze Wolf]]'', the only distinction of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]], awarded by the World Scout Committee for exceptional services to world Scouting.
