{{Infobox person | name = Moayad Shatat | image = | birth_date = 28/07/1984 | birth_place = Qatar | nationality = Jordanian | education = Degree in Economic Science | occupation = Director of the Elche CF Project with Skyline International }}
'''Moayad Shatat''' (born 28 July 1984, Qatar) is a Jordanian businessman, who has links to the world of football, particularly the [[La Liga|Spanish League]]. He served as vice president with [[Málaga CF]] and in 2016 was selected by Skyline International, part of a business investment group, to manage the project designed for [[Elche CF]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elconfidencial.com/espana/comunidad-valenciana/2016-09-03/david-phillips-elche-cf-skyline-ivf-futbol-espanol-dinero-arabe-ivf_1254567/|title=David Phillips, el galés misterioso que quiere seducir al fútbol español con capital árabe. Noticias de Comunidad Valenciana|last=|first=|date=|work=|newspaper=El Confidencial|access-date=2016-09-03|via=}}</ref> Following the investment made with the group’s international capital into Elche CF, Shatat will take up the role of Executive Chairman of the entity.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elmundo.es/comunidad-valenciana/2016/08/05/57a4d48746163f543d8b45ef.html|title=Skyline Internacional, con sede en Qatar, nuevo dueño del Elche CF|last=|first=|date=|work=|newspaper=ELMUNDO|access-date=2016-08-05|via=}}</ref>
== Professional career == After graduating with a degree in [[Economics|Economic Sciences]] in 2005 from the University of Applied Sciences in Amman, Jordan, he began working on the supervision and development of major projects in the [[United Arab Emirates]] and Qatar.
In 2015, Moayad Shatat was named ‘Honorary Consul’ of the Parliament of Brazil for the [[Middle East]]. In February 2016, he received a ‘[[Honorary degree|Doctor Honoris Causa]]’ title in International Business and Finance, by the Charisma International University.
==Málaga CF== Shatat was appointed by the owner of Málaga CF, [[Abdullah bin Nasser bin Abdullah Al Ahmed Al Thani|Abdullah bin Naser Al Thani]], as vice president of the entity in 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/20120726/malaga/malaga-deudas-cazorla-fichajes-jeque_54330297019.html|title=Llega Moayad Shatat para pagar las deudas y activar las altas y bajas|last=|first=|date=|work=|newspaper=Mundo Deportivo|access-date=2012-07-26|via=}}</ref> Shatat remained in this role until his resignation in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.laopiniondemalaga.es/malagacf/2015/06/03/shatat-presenta-dimision/770847.html|title=Shatat presenta su dimisión|last=Málaga|first=La Opinión de|date=|work=|access-date=2015-06-03|via=}}</ref> The executive joined the Club during a full institutional crisis, and through a profound economic restructuring, was able to implement a sustainable management model, adapting to the new regulation of financial control.
With Shatat as vice president, Málaga CF achieved its greatest sporting achievement; reaching the quarter finals of the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.malagahoy.es/article/malagacf/1480724/la/prensa/elogia/historico/pase/cuartos/supermalaga.html|title=MálagaCF - La prensa elogia el histórico pase a cuartos del|last=|first=|date=|website=www.malagahoy.es|publisher=|access-date=2013-03-14}}</ref>
==Elche CF== Shatat currently holds the position of director of the Elche CF Project, that Skyline International has designed for the Club.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.superdeporte.es/futbol/2016/08/05/elche-nuevo-accionista-catar-millones/305911.html|title=El Elche ya tiene nuevo dueño|last=Superdeporte|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2016-08-05|via=}}</ref> The Jordanian businessman will serve as Executive Chairman,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/elche/2016/09/14/57d938d4ca4741202e8b4654.html|title=Elche: Shatat da el sí a Skyline - Marca.com|last=|first=|date=|work=|newspaper=Marca.com|access-date=2016-09-14|via=}}</ref> once the international group has finalised their majority ownership of the Football Club.
